4.2. Log in to the Cluster
Note: this step is now required to be run every 24 hours.
Visit the HCP Console HCC Kubernetes Manage link.
This page lists all the namespaces in various clusters your MSID can view or contribute in HCP Console.
Identify the cluster name and map to the corresponding CLUSTER_API_HOSTNAME.
Request Cloud Native ID access to the "Console AD Group" found in the namespace details if you haven't done so based on instructions in Prerequisites section.
Use the command in the example section below to login to the corresponding cluster:
copy code snippet button
gcloud anthos auth login --server https://Cluster_API_Hostname --login-config-cert=Path_to_Cert_File
When you run following commands, a warning will popup in your browser and you can accept that and click proceed. It allows you to trust these local clusters' certificates.
